div.p:
1 Predeſtination is twofold: of matters; of men. Predeſtination of things or matters is Gods decree, whereby he hath ordained vniverſally all things from euerlaſting to their proper ende, that ſhould be made or done. As, the things that Herod and Pontius Pilate with the Gentiles and people of Iſrael did, the hand and counſell of God decreed all ſhould be done, thas is to ſay, did predeſtinate or appoint beforehand to be done. Act. 4.27. So ſaith Paul, 1. Cor. 2.7. that God did (
                     〈 in non-Latin alphabet 〉
                  ) that is, predeſtinate or decree the wiſdome which is hid in a myſterie, before the world to our glorie.
